## Context
First stage of the top-level tidy (tracker `0223`). Data-side already in
progress per the author. This ticket captures the data workstream so its scope
does not bleed into the code and prose stages.

The data workstream does **not** touch `scripts/` or `content/` — those are
`0225` and `0226`. It is confined to `config/`, `data/`, and DVC wiring, which
are Quarto- and import-independent, so it can land first and in parallel.

## Actions
1. Confirm what "en cours" already covers; record the current state here.
2. Decide whether `config/` artifacts that are generated (`v1_cluster_*`,
   `v1_identifiers.txt.gz`, `v1_tab_alluvial.csv`) belong in `config/` (hand
   authored) or move under `data/`/`output/` (generated). Config should hold
   inputs, not build products.
3. Keep DVC stage paths coherent with any move (the risky part — `dvc.yaml` /
   `dvc.lock`).

## Test
- `make corpus-sync` (doudou) or the relevant data target still resolves after
  any path change; `dvc status` clean.

## Invariants
- Data flows padme→doudou only; do not trigger Phase 1 from a doudou build.
- No `scripts/` or `content/` moves here.

## Exit criteria
- Data-side layout settled and documented; DVC coherent; tracker `0223` updated.
